%N A396231 Sort digits in descending order then add to original number, repeat, starting with 1.
%H A396231 Michael S. Branicky, <a href="/A396231/b396231.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..1012</a>
%F A396231 a(n+1) = a(n) + A004186(a(n)), a(1) = 1. - _Michael S. Branicky_, May 21 2026
%e A396231 Start with first term 1, sort in descending order and add to 1, 1+1 = 2 (second term is 2).
%e A396231 Repeat: 2+2 = 4, 4+4 = 8, 8+8 = 16, 16+61 = 77, 77+77 = 154, 154+541 = 695 and so on.
%t A396231 NestList[#+FromDigits[Reverse[Sort[IntegerDigits[#]]]] &, 1, 27] (* _Stefano Spezia_, May 20 2026 *)
%o A396231 (Python)
%o A396231 from itertools import islice
%o A396231 def agen(): # generator of terms
%o A396231     an = 1
%o A396231     while True:
%o A396231         yield an
%o A396231         an += int("".join(sorted(str(an), reverse=True)))
%o A396231 print(list(islice(agen(), 28))) # _Michael S. Branicky_, May 21 2026
%Y A396231 Cf. A004186, A033860 (same for ascending order).
